"Configure your SMTP server settings for sending emails. To set up SMTP: 1) "
"Enable SMTP by checking the \"Enable SMTP\" checkbox, 2) Enter your SMTP "
"Host (e.g., smtp.gmail.com for Gmail, smtp.mail.yahoo.com for Yahoo), 3) Set "
"the SMTP Port (commonly 587 for TLS or 465 for SSL), 4) Select the Security "
"type (TLS, SSL, or None), 5) If your server requires authentication, enable "
"\"SMTP Authentication\" and enter your Username and Password (for Gmail, you "
"must use an App Password, not your regular password), 6) Optionally set the "
"From Email and From Name that will appear as the sender. After configuration,"
" test your settings by sending a test email."
msgstr ""

